  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Access to sanitary pads for refugee girls</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will ensure consistent monthly supply of sanitary pads to 1000 refugee girls in their final year of primary schooling. Each girl will receive one pack of pads monthly over 12 months period which will help these girls complete and sit for their final primary leaving exams. In 2018, more than 200 refugee girls at Adjumani could not sit for their primary leaving examinations due to lack of sanitary pads and poor performance among girls was attributed to absenteeism during menstruation.</narrative>
  </description>
